    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>Favored by spellcasters who like to experiment and push the boundaries of their spellcasting, a spellcaster’s serum is a sweet tasting, translucent fluid that comes in varying colors. Drinking a spellcaster’s serum fills you with additional magical energy that you can use to enhance the next spell you cast. This energy lasts until the end of your next turn. If you don’t cast a spell in this time, this magical energy is wasted with no effect. A spell can be modified by only one spellcaster’s serum at a time and each spellcaster’s serum can modify only one spell.</p>\n<p><strong>Stretching (Level 8; 1,500 credits)</strong>: A stretching spellcaster’s serum is blue. The first time you cast a spell while this serum is in effect, you expand its area. If the spell is a burst, emanation, or spread, you increase the spell’s radius by 5 feet. If the spell is a cone or line, you increase the spell’s range by 5 feet. Spells that don’t have one of these areas are unaffected by this serum.</p>"
